article.headline: St. Francis, N.Y. 66, Wagner 51
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Robert Hines had 17 points and nine rebounds as St. Francis, N.Y., rallied for a 66-51 victory over Wagner on Saturday. Allan Sheppard added 10 points for the Terriers (4-16, 2-6 Northeast), who held 30-26 lead at halftime en route to snapping a three-game losing streak. Jamal Smith had 11 points and James Ulrich added 10 for the host Seahawks (5-12, 2-4). Ulrichs' 3-point basket gave Wagner its last lead, 36-34 at with 16:48 left in the second half. John Gooden had seven points and Sheppard six in a 19-2 run that put St. Francis in command, 53-38 with 10:23 left.
